<HEADLINE>
FT  05 NOV 94 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: Mother won't open account
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
My elderly mother has never had a bank account and insists she does not want
one, so I have cashed cheques for her through my own bank account. But with
the increase in 'account payee only' cheques, this is becoming increasingly
difficult.
I have heard there are agencies which cash cheques for individuals for a
small percentage fee. Would this be an option?
The recent legislation reforming cheque law is aimed at narrowing the
possibility of cheque fraud. Thus, 'account payee only' cheques are
omni-present and your mother will have no alternative but to open an
account. But this is not intimidating and any one of the clearers should be
able to help. (Murray Johnstone).
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All enquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
</TEXT>
