FT  05 NOV 94 / Saudis reject US arms base
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Saudi Arabia has refused to accept basing of arms for US troops who might
again be sent to the Gulf, but the US will press the Saudis to reverse that
position, a senior US defence official said yesterday. The official also
said Kuwait would pay the largest share of the estimated Dollars 600m cost
of a recent US military build-up in the Gulf against Iraq, but that
Washington also expected Saudi Arabia to help pay the bill. Kuwait and Qatar
have each agreed to provide basing for enough tanks and other supplies for a
US brigade and the Pentagon is searching for a base in the region for enough
equipment for a third brigade. The Saudis currently provide basing for
dozens of US military aircraft but have been reluctant to accept supplies
for American ground troops because of opposition to such a move by Moslem
fundamentalists.
