<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 94 / International Company News: Cigna buys back former S Africa
subsidiary
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Cigna became the first big US insurer to re-open for business in South
Africa with the announcement yesterday that it had bought back its former
subsidiary in the country, writes Richard Waters in New York.
The subsidiary was sold to its employees in 1987 following the imposition of
sanctions against the country by the US government, and by state and local
authorities.
The subsidiary, which was renamed Concord Insurance Company of South Africa
in 1987, will take back the Cigna name.
