<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 94 / International Company News: Continental Airlines names new
chief
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Continental Airlines, the fifth biggest US carrier, yesterday said it had
promoted Mr Gordon Bethune, previously chief operating officer, to the post
of president and chief executive. He replaces Mr Robert Ferguson, who
abruptly resigned as vice-chairman and chief executive last week, writes
Richard Tomkins in New York.
Mr Bethune, who started in the industry as a mechanic, takes over the job at
a time when Continental is struggling to improve the performance of its
low-cost Continental Lite operations. His predecessor had been a strong
backer of the Lite services, which account for more than half the airline's
daily flights.
