<TEXT>
Mr Norm Fussell, chairman of Highlands Gold, the Papua New Guinea-based
mining company which is controlled by Australia's MIM Holdings, said
yesterday that directors were increasingly confident that a mine could be
developed at Nena, the copper/gold prospect close to the Frieda River in the
