FT  04 NOV 94 / International Company News: Horsham lifted by gain from
Barrick share deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Third-quarter earnings at Horsham, the Canadian investment holding company,
controlled by Mr Peter Munk, were lifted by a large one-time accounting gain
stemming from an issue of shares by American Barrick, the gold producer
controlled by Horsham, when it acquired Lac Minerals.
The third-quarter gain reflects the difference between the price at which
Barrick shares were issued to former Lac shareholders, and the lower value
at which Horsham carries Barrick on its books.
Net earnings, including the USDollars 136m gain, were USDollars 152.2m, or
Dollars 1.42 a share, up from Dollars 15.7m, or 15 cents, a year earlier.
Earnings were 15 cents a share without the gain. Revenues climbed to Dollars
697.9m from Dollars 552m.
Horsham's horizons have broadened with its purchase of a 47 per cent stake
in Trizec, the Calgary-based property developer, and American Barrick's
acquisition of Lac.
