FT  04 NOV 94 / International Company News: Moore reverses three-year sales
slide in quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
New strategies, restructuring and changes at the top have reversed a
three-year slide in sales at Moore, the Toronto-based international business
forms and information services group.
Third-quarter net profit was USDollars 30.5m, or 31 cents a share, on sales
of Dollars 584m, against USDollars 16.5m, or 17 cents, on sales of Dollars
566m a year earlier.
Moore has changed its traditional forms operations towards electronic-based
systems, direct mail and labelling. It has eliminated 1,500 jobs worldwide.
Nine-month net profit was USDollars 82.2m, or 83 cents a share, against
USDollars 60.6m, or 61 cents.
