bankers refused to renew its lines of credit. The company added that its two
banks had agreed to extend the company's facilities until the end of
December while a range of possibilities for restructuring the company's
finances were examined. Enterprise, originally a seller of used mainframe
computers, has been repositioning itself in computing services but the
change has been more difficult than expected.
