FT  04 NOV 94 / Insurer shifts to salaries for agents
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Colonial, a Kent-based life insurance company, yesterday became the latest
organisation in the sector to announce a shift to a system of paying
salaries and bonuses rather than commission-only to its employed direct
sales force, Alison Smith writes.
From next year the 570 employed sales agents will move to salaries of up to
Pounds 18,000 - with bonuses typically taking total pay to about Pounds
25,000. The 80 self-employed sales agents for Colonial will continue to be
paid on a commission-only basis.
Mr Sandy Grant, deputy general manager, said he was sure that in dealing
with customers the two types of sales agent would both make sure investors
were clear about their remuneration structures.
